19
00:00:18,564 --> 00:00:21,108
<i>War in the Inner Rim!</i>

20
00:00:21,234 --> 00:00:24,946
<i>Rebel leader Steela Gerrera
has joined forces with General Tandin</i>

21
00:00:25,446 --> 00:00:29,116
<i>after boldly rescuing Onderon's
former king from execution,</i>

22
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,119
<i>evading a trap set
by Separatist ally King Rash</i>

23
00:00:32,245 --> 00:00:34,288
<i>and the droid General Kalani.</i>

24
00:00:34,413 --> 00:00:37,041
<i>Amid growing public support
and rising unrest,</i>

25
00:00:37,124 --> 00:00:39,794
<i>Ahsoka continues to monitor
the rebels' efforts</i>

26
00:00:39,877 --> 00:00:44,423
<i>as they rally around Ramsis Dendup
to restore his reign as the rightful king</i>

27
00:00:44,715 --> 00:00:48,928
<i>and finally put an end to the Separatist
occupation of Onderon.</i>

28
00:01:03,651 --> 00:01:06,320
I'm picking up an electromagnetic field.

29
00:01:06,362 --> 00:01:09,115
Roger, roger. It's coming from there.

30
00:01:16,455 --> 00:01:17,498
Whoa!

31
00:01:17,540 --> 00:01:19,875
<i>My fellow subjects,</i>

32
00:01:20,001 --> 00:01:22,169
<i>I appear not as your king,</i>

33
00:01:22,295 --> 00:01:24,880
<i>but as a servant of Onderon.</i>

34
00:01:25,047 --> 00:01:27,842
<i>We are in the midst of a great struggle.</i>

35
00:01:27,883 --> 00:01:32,305
<i>The Confederacy has used
the recent attacks as an opportunity</i>

36
00:01:32,346 --> 00:01:35,558
<i>to tighten their hold on Onderon.</i>

37
00:01:35,975 --> 00:01:39,729
<i>They have accused me of leading
these so-called terrorists.</i>

38
00:01:40,521 --> 00:01:46,360
<i>It is a lie they have engineered to further
restrict your independence</i>

39
00:01:46,402 --> 00:01:49,614
<i>and use deadly force against our people.</i>

40
00:01:50,031 --> 00:01:53,409
<i>The truth is,
I have never met them before now.</i>

41
00:01:53,868 --> 00:01:57,913
<i>I have come to know them
as the true sons of Onderon.</i>

42
00:01:58,372 --> 00:02:01,042
<i>They are unwilling
to surrender our freedom</i>

43
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:03,461
<i>to those who conspire to take it from us.</i>

44
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:09,091
<i>Our destiny is tied to them and this planet.</i>

45
00:02:09,467 --> 00:02:12,887
<i>We must all rise together to protect it.</i>

46
00:02:18,392 --> 00:02:19,727
Uh-oh.

47
00:02:19,769 --> 00:02:21,937
Why are they looking at us that way?

48
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:24,440
Hey!

49
00:02:26,317 --> 00:02:28,110
What the... Blast him!

50
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:35,743
Uh-oh.

51
00:02:56,639 --> 00:03:00,309
The people are turning against the droids.
There's rioting in the streets now.

52
00:03:00,393 --> 00:03:02,061
That's a beautiful thing.

53
00:03:02,645 --> 00:03:05,690
We need to keep the battle
to the outskirts of the city.

54
00:03:06,357 --> 00:03:08,192
Less structures and people.

55
00:03:08,693 --> 00:03:11,904
But less clankers.
Their main force is in Iziz.

56
00:03:11,987 --> 00:03:15,533
We should join the fight down there
and take it straight to King Rash.

57
00:03:15,616 --> 00:03:19,245
We all want victory,
but not at the cost of innocent lives.

58
00:03:19,453 --> 00:03:22,123
If we fight door to door, no one is safe.

59
00:03:22,623 --> 00:03:24,291
This is war, Steela.

60
00:03:24,542 --> 00:03:26,794
-She's right.
-I agree.

61
00:03:27,086 --> 00:03:29,714
The more you draw the droids
from the city to the highlands,

62
00:03:29,797 --> 00:03:31,465
the safer the people will be.

63
00:03:31,674 --> 00:03:33,759
My men await your command, my lord.

64
00:03:34,343 --> 00:03:37,513
I believe there is a new contender.

65
00:03:38,222 --> 00:03:42,435
You will lead our forces.
Including the royal army.

66
00:03:42,685 --> 00:03:45,896
Steela is now the commanding general.

67
00:03:46,063 --> 00:03:47,940
A great choice.

68
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,985
As you wish, my lord.

69
00:03:51,485 --> 00:03:55,197
You and your rebels renewed
my faith in myself.

70
00:03:55,322 --> 00:03:58,325
Now, I'm putting my faith in you.

71
00:03:58,826 --> 00:04:00,661
Thank you, Your Majesty.

72
00:04:01,829 --> 00:04:03,038
Let's ride.

73
00:04:19,638 --> 00:04:20,890
Just in case.

74
00:04:47,708 --> 00:04:50,044
We are losing the public.

75
00:04:50,461 --> 00:04:53,881
If they turn against us, I fear the outcome.

76
00:04:54,173 --> 00:04:56,884
Fear will bring them back.

77
00:04:57,051 --> 00:05:00,387
We must eliminate Dendup,
General Tandin and the terrorists

78
00:05:00,554 --> 00:05:02,723
before the people commit to their efforts.

79
00:05:02,807 --> 00:05:05,142
General Tandin is weak.

80
00:05:05,267 --> 00:05:09,313
His army will not withstand the power
of the Confederacy.

81
00:05:09,396 --> 00:05:11,941
Neither will the terrorists.

82
00:05:12,024 --> 00:05:15,528
General, our scouts have located
the main rebel forces

83
00:05:15,611 --> 00:05:17,863
in the mountains to the east.

84
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,615
With the rioting in the city,

85
00:05:19,698 --> 00:05:22,368
how can we spare the troops
to attack the rebels in the mountains?

86
00:05:22,868 --> 00:05:25,788
Do not underestimate our means.

87
00:05:25,871 --> 00:05:30,459
If the rebel army falls,
the citizens will lose their courage.

88
00:05:30,918 --> 00:05:32,962
Then order will be restored.

89
00:05:41,971 --> 00:05:44,974
Your target lies in the mountains
to the east.

90
00:05:45,057 --> 00:05:48,978
The army will follow. Leave no survivors.

91
00:05:49,061 --> 00:05:51,272
-Go!
<i>-By your command.</i>

92
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,415
The droid army is almost here.

93
00:06:09,498 --> 00:06:11,208
Everyone, get ready.

94
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:28,475
Ready!

95
00:06:28,684 --> 00:06:30,769
Saw, begin your attack.

96
00:07:32,039 --> 00:07:33,082
No!

97
00:07:33,415 --> 00:07:34,875
Where did that come from?

98
00:07:34,959 --> 00:07:36,043
There!

99
00:07:39,463 --> 00:07:40,631
Any ideas?

100
00:07:40,965 --> 00:07:42,383
Yeah. Run!

101
00:08:32,641 --> 00:08:35,269
<i>I take it the rebels
have Dooku's full attention.</i>

102
00:08:35,394 --> 00:08:39,982
It's a full-scale war! They need our help!
Please talk to the Council.

103
00:08:40,107 --> 00:08:42,818
<i>Even Master Windu would be wary
at this point.</i>

104
00:08:42,943 --> 00:08:46,905
<i>The Council will not engage or involve
the Republic in an internal affair.</i>

105
00:08:47,406 --> 00:08:50,284
The Separatists have a new gunship
with a powerful ray shield.

106
00:08:50,325 --> 00:08:52,119
Nothing's getting past it.

107
00:08:52,244 --> 00:08:55,497
<i>I am sorry, Ahsoka.
They will have to find a way.</i>

108
00:08:55,622 --> 00:08:58,459
<i>Do not stay there if their failure is certain.</i>

109
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:01,962
<i>Evacuate who you can
and return to Coruscant immediately.</i>

110
00:09:02,087 --> 00:09:03,255
<i>Do you understand?</i>

111
00:09:03,672 --> 00:09:04,965
<i>Yes, Master.</i>

112
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,926
We need to help them.

113
00:09:08,177 --> 00:09:11,180
We will do what we can
to relocate the survivors.

114
00:09:11,305 --> 00:09:13,140
Before they lose their planet.

115
00:09:13,265 --> 00:09:14,641
We can't.

116
00:09:15,142 --> 00:09:18,479
What difference does it make now?
The Separatists know we're involved.

117
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:21,440
I don't disagree with you, Anakin.

118
00:09:21,774 --> 00:09:24,818
But to send in Republic gunships
defeats our purpose.

119
00:09:25,277 --> 00:09:29,615
We must stay true to our intentions.
Learn our lessons.

120
00:09:30,074 --> 00:09:32,576
It doesn't have to look like
we're the ones helping.

121
00:09:32,951 --> 00:09:35,120
What if another party was involved?

122
00:09:35,454 --> 00:09:36,747
Another party?

123
00:09:37,915 --> 00:09:41,668
Who in the galaxy would be running around
with an extra batch of missiles?

124
00:09:44,755 --> 00:09:45,964
Hondo.

125
00:09:55,474 --> 00:09:57,434
Is the Republic going to help us?

126
00:09:57,518 --> 00:09:58,769
No.

127
00:09:59,186 --> 00:10:00,604
What's it going to take?

128
00:10:01,271 --> 00:10:02,940
King Rash rules Onderon.

129
00:10:03,023 --> 00:10:06,026
Unless that changes,
the Republic can't do anything.

130
00:10:06,485 --> 00:10:08,445
They're pulling back. Cover them.

131
00:10:22,126 --> 00:10:24,711
At this rate, the clankers
aren't gonna need reinforcements.

132
00:10:25,045 --> 00:10:26,672
We have to regroup at the Nest.

133
00:10:58,912 --> 00:11:03,250
Skywalker, my old friend. You come alone?

134
00:11:03,584 --> 00:11:04,877
For your service.

135
00:11:04,918 --> 00:11:07,880
Oh ! Business? Good, good, good.

136
00:11:08,255 --> 00:11:10,424
That, I understand.

137
00:11:10,549 --> 00:11:12,426
I need you to make a delivery for me.

138
00:11:14,261 --> 00:11:19,224
And that is all I am to you Jedi?
A delivery boy?

139
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:21,935
I know that if I need arms shipped illegally,

140
00:11:22,227 --> 00:11:23,896
you're the man I need to go to.

141
00:11:24,229 --> 00:11:26,231
Illegally?

142
00:11:26,481 --> 00:11:29,443
Now why would a Jedi need
to deliver arms

143
00:11:29,943 --> 00:11:31,403
illegally?

144
00:11:31,945 --> 00:11:34,615
How about I pay you well enough
that you just deliver the missiles for me

145
00:11:34,656 --> 00:11:36,450
and don't ask any questions?

146
00:11:38,619 --> 00:11:41,788
Well, as long as you're not paying me
in credits,

147
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:45,959
I'm sure I could accommodate
your wishes, Master Jedi.

148
00:11:53,258 --> 00:11:56,929
The highlands may slow down the droids
but they won't stop the gunships.

149
00:11:57,095 --> 00:11:58,305
We have to move.

150
00:11:58,764 --> 00:12:00,515
Any word from Master Skywalker?

151
00:12:00,807 --> 00:12:01,892
Not yet.

152
00:12:04,895 --> 00:12:06,313
We're not giving up yet.

153
00:12:06,813 --> 00:12:09,733
Stagger our defenses to the camp.
Secure the approach.

154
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:12,986
Stay in small teams.
Make use of our training.

155
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:15,656
You really are the best leader among us.

156
00:12:15,906 --> 00:12:18,325
Couldn't be more proud of you, my sister.

157
00:12:19,076 --> 00:12:21,662
I learned from the best, big brother.

158
00:12:22,579 --> 00:12:24,164
Let's go, General.

159
00:12:25,582 --> 00:12:27,000
You have to help us.

160
00:12:27,167 --> 00:12:29,336
I'll do all I can to protect you.

161
00:12:29,503 --> 00:12:31,838
But I can't fight this war for you.

162
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,176
We wouldn't have made it this far
without you.

163
00:12:36,551 --> 00:12:38,178
I wish I could do more.

164
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:41,682
Wait, looks like we have company.

165
00:12:52,693 --> 00:12:53,735
Don't shoot!

166
00:13:02,661 --> 00:13:04,037
Well!

167
00:13:04,121 --> 00:13:08,041
You could be my new favorite spice.

168
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,127
Yeah, I don't think so.

169
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:11,503
Careful, pirate.

170
00:13:11,586 --> 00:13:14,172
Hondo, what are you doing here?

171
00:13:14,464 --> 00:13:15,674
No, no, no, no.

172
00:13:15,757 --> 00:13:17,759
You should thank me, child.

173
00:13:18,093 --> 00:13:21,888
I have brought you a gift
from Skywalker and Kenobi.

174
00:13:22,347 --> 00:13:24,266
The latest from Sienar.

175
00:13:24,474 --> 00:13:25,517
Rocket launchers?

176
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,770
Shoulder fire. Very expensive.

177
00:13:29,062 --> 00:13:30,314
Paid for?

178
00:13:30,522 --> 00:13:32,482
Very handsome... Oh!

179
00:13:33,025 --> 00:13:34,609
Oh, my, look at the time.

180
00:13:37,029 --> 00:13:38,739
Well, my work here is done.

181
00:13:58,091 --> 00:14:00,469
Ugh ! They must have seen Hondo's ship.

182
00:14:00,969 --> 00:14:02,429
It was only a patrol.

183
00:14:02,846 --> 00:14:04,931
We have to get these down to the others.

184
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:07,517
-Load them up.
-I hope they work.

185
00:14:07,601 --> 00:14:09,978
There's only one way to find out.

186
00:14:21,448 --> 00:14:24,785
We've tried everything, but we're
target practice for those gunships.

187
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:26,536
Now it's their turn.

188
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:27,788
Thank the Jedi.

189
00:14:30,207 --> 00:14:31,291
Saw!

190
00:14:41,635 --> 00:14:43,804
I love this!

191
00:14:44,471 --> 00:14:45,722
-Yeah !
-Yeah!

192
00:14:48,934 --> 00:14:52,312
Distribute the rocket launchers
and take out those gunships.

193
00:14:52,479 --> 00:14:55,273
<i>Steela, they're attacking the Nest!
They're after the King!</i>

194
00:14:55,357 --> 00:14:56,650
Come on!

195
00:15:03,281 --> 00:15:05,075
She sure leads by example.

196
00:15:05,158 --> 00:15:07,828
What good will that do us
if she gets herself killed?

197
00:15:19,339 --> 00:15:20,632
Steela, hurry!

198
00:15:21,007 --> 00:15:22,175
Steela, come in!

199
00:15:22,426 --> 00:15:23,468
Ugh!

200
00:15:23,510 --> 00:15:25,303
Where is the false king?

201
00:15:26,596 --> 00:15:27,806
I'll never tell you!

202
00:15:28,598 --> 00:15:29,641
Ugh!

203
00:15:29,683 --> 00:15:31,351
Find the king.

204
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,705
Help has arrived!

205
00:16:39,628 --> 00:16:41,254
Are you all right, Your Majesty?

206
00:16:42,088 --> 00:16:43,465
Thanks to you.

207
00:16:44,299 --> 00:16:45,425
Fire!

208
00:16:48,470 --> 00:16:49,971
Last one's mine.

209
00:16:56,311 --> 00:16:57,395
Look out!

210
00:17:13,578 --> 00:17:14,621
Look!

211
00:17:27,008 --> 00:17:28,760
Hang on!

212
00:17:30,637 --> 00:17:31,805
Steela!

213
00:17:46,695 --> 00:17:47,862
I'll handle this.

214
00:17:52,450 --> 00:17:53,493
I got you.

215
00:18:37,912 --> 00:18:42,042
Your gunships have failed.
I need more reinforcements!

216
00:18:42,375 --> 00:18:47,130
<i>Really? General Kalani,
what is your assessment of the situation?</i>

217
00:18:47,297 --> 00:18:49,799
They have managed to
penetrate our shields,

218
00:18:49,883 --> 00:18:54,054
and are using the cover of the highlands
against our forces.

219
00:18:54,095 --> 00:18:57,807
To defeat them will take time.

220
00:18:58,141 --> 00:19:01,561
<i>A prolonged war
does not interest me, General.</i>

221
00:19:01,936 --> 00:19:05,440
<i>The rebellion grows
with every small victory.</i>

222
00:19:05,607 --> 00:19:08,276
Then we are lost.

223
00:19:08,485 --> 00:19:11,571
<i>Salvage the remaining arms
and withdraw the army.</i>

224
00:19:11,946 --> 00:19:13,823
<i>Bring them to Agamar.</i>

225
00:19:15,575 --> 00:19:16,951
What about...

226
00:19:28,004 --> 00:19:31,424
It was my fault. I shot that gunship down.

227
00:19:31,925 --> 00:19:33,968
It crashed into her position.

228
00:19:34,427 --> 00:19:36,596
Saw, it's not your fault.

229
00:19:37,430 --> 00:19:39,265
She knew what the risks were.

230
00:19:39,474 --> 00:19:42,769
We all knew what it would take
to free Onderon.

231
00:20:28,314 --> 00:20:30,984
This has been quite a journey
for our Padawan.

232
00:20:31,651 --> 00:20:34,320
Steela will be a powerful spirit
in their lives.

233
00:20:34,821 --> 00:20:36,072
Yes.

234
00:20:36,823 --> 00:20:38,158
For all of us.

235
00:20:43,663 --> 00:20:45,498
I'm sorry for your loss.

236
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:48,710
Thanks.

237
00:20:48,793 --> 00:20:49,919
But it's over now.

238
00:20:50,170 --> 00:20:52,046
Let's just leave it at that.

239
00:20:54,549 --> 00:20:56,259
Steela would be glad.

240
00:20:56,342 --> 00:20:59,304
Her sacrifice gave Onderon its freedom.

241
00:21:00,346 --> 00:21:01,973
But at what cost?

242
00:21:02,557 --> 00:21:04,184
It's like you once said.

243
00:21:04,476 --> 00:21:07,604
"Many lives get caught between
the Republic and the Separatists."

244
00:21:07,687 --> 00:21:09,189
I did say that once.

245
00:21:09,355 --> 00:21:12,734
Then after watching the heroics
and selflessness of the Jedi,

246
00:21:12,817 --> 00:21:16,488
I do believe the Republic
is the right side to be on.

247
00:21:16,571 --> 00:21:17,864
What do you mean?

248
00:21:18,156 --> 00:21:20,867
Dendup has appointed me
the new Senator of Onderon.

249
00:21:21,075 --> 00:21:23,203
I will follow in my mother's footsteps.

250
00:21:23,328 --> 00:21:25,622
And I will bring us back to the Republic.

251
00:21:26,122 --> 00:21:28,291
Remember this day!

252
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:32,045
The day Onderon became free again!

253
00:21:34,321 --> 00:21:39,321
http://hiqve.com/

